						<div class="postbody">Given that they put the audio mix on the NES's expansion connector, and they only reserved 10 pads, and the cable from the FDS base to the drive itself is 11 conductors, two of which are power and ground... I guess they could have done it that way. (q.v. electronics junkers' RE'd schematic: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://green.ap.teacup.com/junker/119.html">http://green.ap.teacup.com/junker/119.html</a><!-- m --> )<br /><br />Seems a little weird to me to have deliberately decided to route audio through the expansion connector twice, but it's pointless to second-guess now.</div>

